requires:
    manifest.is_Genio == 'True'
    manifest.has_genio_onsemi_ap1302_isp_and_ar0430_camera_module_as_yuv_sensor == 'True'
depends: genio-mipi-camera/firmware-checking-ap1302-ar0430
estimated_duration: 0.1
_summary: Onsemi AP1302 with AR0430 record video via v4l2-ctl
_purpose:
    Record video via v4l2-ctl
_steps:
    1. Install v4l-utils package if not already installed:
       sudo apt install v4l-utils
    2. Find the AP1302-AR0430 camera video nodes:
       (If support ImgSensor)
       v4l2-ctl --list-devices | grep mtk-v4l2-camera -A 4
       (If support v4l2 sensor)
       v4l2-ctl --list-devices | grep camsv -A 1
       Note: AP1302-AR0430 will only have 1 video node for Preview, Video, and Capture on the same node.
    3. (If support v4l2 sensor), 
       Get the media node
       v4l2-ctl --list-devices | grep -E *camsys -A 1
       Set camera capture format through media-ctl for CSI0
       media-ctl -d /dev/media<N> -V "'ap1302.2-003d':2 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/2316x1746]"
       media-ctl -d /dev/media<N> -V "'15040000.seninf':4 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/2316x1746]"
       media-ctl -d /dev/media<N> -V "'15050000.camsv':1 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/2316x1746]"
       Set camera capture format through media-ctl for CSI0 
       media-ctl -d /dev/media<N> -V "'ap1302.3-003d':2 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/2316x1746]"
       media-ctl -d /dev/media<N> -V "'15040000.seninf':5 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/2316x1746]"
       media-ctl -d /dev/media<N> -V "'15050800.camsv':1 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/2316x1746]"
    4. (If support ImgSensor)Check supported formats for the capture node:
       v4l2-ctl -d /dev/videoX --list-formats-ext
    5. Capture a video in different formats:
       # For UYVY format
       v4l2-ctl -d /dev/videoX \
         --set-fmt-video=width=2316,height=1746,pixelformat=UYVY \
         --set-parm=30 \
         --stream-mmap \
         --stream-count=100 \
         --stream-to=/tmp/ap1302_ar0430.yuv \
         --verbose
_verification:
    1. Does the command can be performed without any problem?
    2. Copy the captured videos to your host and check their quality via ffplay:
       # For UYVY format
       ffplay -f rawvideo -video_size 2316x1746 -pixel_format uyvy422 -i /tmp/ap1302_ar0430.yuv

